Good question! Define a custom serializer for enums with `Serialize`/`Deserialize`. Here’s an example:

```rust
use serde::{Serialize, Serializer};
enum Status {
    Active,
    Suspended,
}

impl Serialize for Status {
    fn serialize(&self, ser: &mut Serializer) -> Result<(), serde::ser::Error> {
        match self {
            Self::Active => ser.serialize_str("active"),
            Self::Suspended => ser.serialize_str("suspended"),
        }
    }
}

#[derive(Serialize, Deserialize)]
struct Account {
    user_id: u64,
    status: Status,
}
```
This lets you control how enums serialize to JSON.

